# External service addresses — non-secret infrastructure inventory.
# Source of truth for cross-VM connectivity to the Compose stack.
# Updated by operator after provisioning (see INFRASTRUCTURE_SETUP.md Step 4).
#
# This file is Git-tracked non-secret inventory. Sensitive values (passwords,
# tokens, DSNs with credentials) must go in Kubernetes Secrets (SOPS path).
#
# NETWORK TRUST BOUNDARY (staging only):
# Public IP, no transport encryption. Compose VM firewall restricts
# to k3s VM IP on these ports. Production requires mTLS or WireGuard.
#
# Per-service keys — all equal today (single Compose VM), modeled as
# independent dependencies so they can diverge without manifest changes.
POSTGRES_ADDR=10.0.0.1
TEMPORAL_ADDR=10.0.0.1
APP_ADDR=10.0.0.1
